description:
Fully managed library providing various random number generators and distributions.
      All the hard work behind this library was done by Stefan Troschütz, and for which I thank him very much. What I am doing with his great project, is simply to refactor and improve his code, while offering a new Python-style random class.
      You can find the modified source code at this address: http://goo.gl/vIV2G
releaseNotes:
This can be considered a stable release, excluding the class TRandom, which is new and incomplete.
      As of 1.4.1.5, TRandom exposes all other distributions, but the class still is undocumented.
      WARNING: Until further notice, class TRandom has to be considered unstable.
      WARNING: This package is young, and the owner is quite new to the NuGet system. If you find any problem, please contact the owner.
